    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Fun experiment, but what should we do about a deliberately broken Python being broken as intended? Any code that encounters the corrupted number will behave incorrectly. It appears that IPython's repl is likely to encounter 8, but `python -i` isn't.\r\n\r\nI don't think we can protect IPython (or any Python code) against numbers being untrustworthy."
